Package: siapopr
Type: Package
Title: siapopr is an R implementation of SIApop to simulate infinite-allele branching process populations  
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Ollie McDonald and Franziska Michor
Maintainer: Ollie McDonald <mcdonald@jimmy.harvard.edu>
Description: siapopr is a branching process simulation software written in C++ to simulate birth-death-mutation processes where each new mutation is unique, following the infinite-allele assumption.
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Imports:
    Rcpp, RcppGSL
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp, RcppGSL
SystemRequirements: GNU GSL
NeedsCompilation: yes
